<p>The <code>stripslashes</code> function removes backslashes from a string.</p>

<h2>Basic Usage</h2>
<pre>{open}echo $slashedText | stripslashes{close}</pre>
<p>Result: <b>{echo $slashedText | stripslashes}</b></p>

<h2>Remove Escapes</h2>
<pre>{open}echo 'It\'s a \"test\"' | stripslashes{close}</pre>
<p>Cleaned: <b>{echo 'It\'s a \"test\"' | stripslashes}</b></p>

<h2>Chained Examples</h2>
<pre>{open}echo 'He said \"hello\"' | stripslashes | upper{close}</pre>
<p>Clean and upper: <b>{echo 'He said \"hello\"' | stripslashes | upper}</b></p>

<h2>Note</h2>
<p>Opposite of <code>slashes</code>. Use to clean escaped strings.</p>
